1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
 Amazing, amazing.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:05,000
 Well, welcome to The Vine once again.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
 We're so glad that you're with us.

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
 It's something that we've been sensing as a leadership,

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,000
 this pastoral presence of the Holy Spirit with us.

6
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
 And I think we felt that really deeply this morning.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
 I know that we're going to continue to feel that deeply

8
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
 as I invite Susanna to come and to be with us.

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
 And I'm going to need to grab this.

10
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
 Can we stretch out our hands?

11
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
 Susanna will be familiar to many of us here at The Vine,

12
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,000
 but if you're relatively new,

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
 Susanna is one of our elders here at the church.

14
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
 We have an amazing group of men and women that lead this church spiritually

15
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
 and govern this church diligently.

16
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
 Susanna has been doing that, I don't know what it is,

17
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
 nine years or something like that.

18
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
 And she's been an incredible blessing to Chris and I and to I know many of you.

19
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,000
 And she has a real pastoral gift.

20
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
 And I know that what's on her heart today is important to all of us.

21
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
 I'm going to show up and pray for you in Jesus' name.

22
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
 Let's pray.

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
 Father, we just thank you so much for Susanna Glenn, the kids,

24
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:06,000
 for the mantle of authority that is placed upon Susanna here at The Vine,

25
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:12,000
 her pastoral gift to teach and to share out of what you've done in her life.

26
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
 Lord, we open up our hearts to all that you have to say to us today

27
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
 through Psalm 27.

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,000
 We thank you for this in Jesus' name.

29
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
 Amen.

30
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
 Good morning.

31
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
 I get the privilege of continuing this series on waiting.

32
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
 And today we're looking at the gift of waiting, pursuit, and presence.

33
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,000
 And we're going to continue to explore Psalm 27 and we're going to focus in

34
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 on verses four to six today.

35
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
 One thing I ask from the Lord, this only do I seek,

36
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:52,000
 that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life,

37
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,000
 to gaze on the beauty of the Lord and to seek him in his temple.

38
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:02,000
 For in the day of trouble he will keep me safe in his dwelling.

39
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:10,000
 He will hide me in the shelter of his sacred tent and set me high upon a rock.

40
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
 Then my head will be exalted above the enemies who surround me.

41
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
 At his sacred tent I will sacrifice with shouts of joy.

42
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
 I will sing and make music to the Lord.

43
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:32,000
 Three weeks ago a friend of mine invited me to a float experience.

44
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
 You enter a large -- you can see up here a picture of it.

45
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:42,000
 You enter a large domed futuristic capsule which is filled with warm water

46
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 that has an extremely high concentration of Epsom salts diluted in it.

47
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
 The pod has a lid.

48
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,000
 You enter.

49
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
 You lie down.

50
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
 You shut the lid.

51
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:01,000
 And when you lay down, you are very buoyant because of the Epsom salts

52
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:05,000
 that are diluted in the water.

53
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:13,000
 And then you float for an hour in complete darkness and quiet.

54
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:19,000
 Some of you who are claustrophobic are going, "Oh, I can't think of anything else."

55
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,000
 There's nothing to distract you.

56
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,000
 There's nothing to do but wait.

57
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:31,000
 And so knowing I was going to speak today on the topic of waiting,

58
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 I started a conversation with God.

59
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,000
 And I said, "What's the deal with waiting?

60
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,000
 Why is it so important?"

61
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 I feel like I'm a true Hong Konger now having said those questions.

62
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
 What's the deal with waiting?

63
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
 Why is it so important?

64
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:57,000
 This is what I heard in response to my questions.

65
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 We wait for what we value.

66
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
 We pursue what we value.

67
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:14,000
 Andrew said in week one that in this world no one likes to wait.

68
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:23,000
 So when we do choose to wait to actively lean in, it's for something we truly value.

69
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:29,000
 God reminded me of a recent moment after church, my family and I,

70
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
 we went to Samson Restaurant.

71
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 We wanted to have Thai food for lunch.

72
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:40,000
 But when we got there, there was a big - you know what it is, right?

73
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,000
 A big queue, a big line.

74
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:48,000
 Because it has incredible Thai food and everybody knows it.

75
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:55,000
 We joined the line and we started waiting, anticipating the yummy food that we would have.

76
00:04:55,000 --> 00:05:01,000
 But after a few minutes of not moving at all

77
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:07,000
 and looking at the long stretch of people in front of us,

78
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
 we decided to leave.

79
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:15,000
 We crossed the road, we entered a building, we went up a flight of stairs

80
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:19,000
 and we went into another Thai restaurant.

81
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
 There was no wait.

82
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
 There was plenty of tables.

83
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:28,000
 And very soon we had food on the table and we were eating.

84
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 However, there was a price to us not waiting.

85
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:44,000
 I've eaten the food of Samson's before and I can tell you it is really good.

86
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:48,000
 And I've now eaten the food of this other Thai place.

87
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:51,000
 And the food was nowhere near as good.

88
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:56,000
 It filled us up, but it was nowhere near as good.

89
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:05,000
 And God said to me, "Susanna, when you lose sight of the value of something, you stop waiting.

90
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:11,000
 And you start to pursue quicker alternative substitutes.

91
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:16,000
 Alternative routes even that are not as good.

92
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:20,000
 You settle for lesser versions."

93
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:26,000
 Andrew spoke to us recently about how many of us had created lesser versions of Jesus.

94
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
 You know, the Jesus that kind of fits with our worldview,

95
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:35,000
 that makes us feel comfortable and doesn't challenge us to change.

96
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:40,000
 This is what happens when we don't wait on Jesus.

97
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:50,000
 Lying in that pod, I felt convicted that I had lost sight of the value of Jesus.

98
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:56,000
 Lost sight of the value of actively slowing down and waiting.

99
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:07,000
 And by losing sight of the value of waiting for Jesus, my life was being filled up with substitutes.

100
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 I was pursuing lesser things.

101
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:20,000
 God gave me a taste in that pod of what it's like when we truly wait.

102
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:23,000
 He reminded me of my worth.

103
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:28,000
 He realigned my identity to match how he saw me.

104
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:34,000
 He encouraged me to believe in the more.

105
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:39,000
 You see, when we have a lesser version of Jesus,

106
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:47,000
 we get contained because it's like we put him in this box that we can handle.

107
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:53,000
 And what also gets contained is your creativity, your belief,

108
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:57,000
 your understanding of what he's capable of doing.

109
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:03,000
 And the real Jesus that I encountered in the waiting in that pod,

110
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:09,000
 he blew out the edges of my dreaming.

111
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:15,000
 And anticipation for the future was reignited in me.

112
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:19,000
 Waiting is for our benefit.

113
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:24,000
 Psalm 103, 14 says, "For he knows our frame.

114
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:28,000
 He remembers that we are dust."

115
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,000
 God compassionately understands us.

116
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
 He created us.

117
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:37,000
 He understands our limitations and our frailties.

118
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:41,000
 This verse, he remembers that we are dust.

119
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:47,000
 It makes me smile because dust gets everywhere.

120
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
 It flies off in every direction.

121
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
 It swirls.

122
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:54,000
 It clings to things it shouldn't.

123
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
 Have you ever run your finger across something in your home and gone,

124
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:02,000
 "Ugh, how did dust get here?"

125
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:08,000
 It makes me smile because it's such an accurate depiction of us.

126
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:13,000
 Yes, God made us from the dust, but the way we live in this modern world,

127
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 with our scattered thoughts, our constant movement, our distractions,

128
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:26,000
 our connection and clinging to things that we shouldn't.

129
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:33,000
 God knows this about us and he whispers, "Be still."

130
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:37,000
 Be still and know me.

131
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:43,000
 Stop rushing and pursuing lesser things.

132
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:46,000
 The waiting is for our benefit.

133
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:55,000
 The first thing that waiting does is realign us to the one thing that's needed.

134
00:09:55,000 --> 00:10:03,000
 "One thing I ask from the Lord," David says, "this only do I seek,

135
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life,

136
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 to gaze on the beauty of the Lord, to seek him."

137
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:19,000
 We wait for and pursue the things we value.

138
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:27,000
 Does the value we carry in our hearts for God's presence match David's in this verse?

139
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 What are you willing to wait for?

140
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,000
 As I was thinking about this, I remembered my husband.

141
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:44,000
 Every time one of my children or I travel overseas,

142
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 he always comes and he waits at the airport to pick us up.

143
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
 Every time.

144
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
 No exception.

145
00:10:54,000 --> 00:11:01,000
 Doesn't matter if we come in on a midnight flight, six in the morning, he's there.

146
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:06,000
 And it made me realise he values us.

147
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,000
 He wants us to know that we're important to him.

148
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,000
 We wait for what we value.

149
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,000
 Just have a look at these verses.

150
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:29,000
 Psalm 2714, "Wait for the Lord, be strong, let your heart take courage, wait for the Lord."

151
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 Lamentations 325, "The Lord is good to those who wait for him, to the soul who seeks him."

152
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:45,000
 Isaiah 3018, "Therefore the Lord waits to be gracious to you.

153
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:49,000
 Therefore he exalts himself to show mercy to you.

154
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:58,000
 For the Lord is a God of justice and blessed are all those who wait for him."

155
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:15,000
 Isaiah 64, "For from of old no one has heard or perceived by the ear, no eye has seen a God besides you, who acts for those who wait for him."

156
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:23,000
 Do we value God enough to wait?

157
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:29,000
 Andrew has said in a previous sermon that waiting is not passive.

158
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,000
 It's active.

159
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:36,000
 Waiting is an active process of preparation.

160
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:43,000
 The second thing that waiting does is it strengthens our resolve for future challenges.

161
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 By deepening our awareness and intimacy with the one who shares the waiting with us.

162
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,000
 Listen to these verses of David again.

163
00:12:53,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 "One thing I ask from the Lord, this only do I seek, that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life.

164
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 To gaze on the beauty of the Lord, to seek him in his temple.

165
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 For in the day of trouble he will keep me safe.

166
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:19,000
 He will hide me and set me high upon a rock."

167
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:28,000
 Waiting, actively seeking God's presence, spending time in the temple prepares David for the day of trouble.

168
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
 The waiting actively prepares David.

169
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 The waiting time teaches him that he can hope in God's timing and his safety.

170
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:52,000
 David is able to anticipate and speak confidently that when the day of trouble comes, he declares that he can trust God.

171
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:55,000
 He declares he will not be alone.

172
00:13:55,000 --> 00:14:00,000
 He declares that the God he's experienced in the waiting, he will keep me safe.

173
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 He will hide me.

174
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,000
 He will set me high.

175
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:10,000
 Waiting gives us the answers we need for future challenges.

176
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:18,000
 It teaches us to trust in God's timing and prepares us for the uncharted and the unknown.

177
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:23,000
 Many years ago, my family was living in Darwin, Australia.

178
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 I was working as a substitute teacher and also working for a Christian NGO that was working into China.

179
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:42,000
 And we began to feel challenged that we were meant to relocate to Hong Kong to deepen our work with this NGO.

180
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 At the time, we had four young kids and we didn't have enough resources to transition our entire family overseas.

181
00:14:52,000 --> 00:15:00,000
 Nevertheless, we began to speak and share as if we were going.

182
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:05,000
 A miracle happened when someone we hardly knew heard of our story.

183
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:11,000
 And when I say we hardly knew him, I'm not exaggerating.

184
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:16,000
 My husband has this gift and I see it in him all the time.

185
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,000
 He notices people on the fringes.

186
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,000
 Do you know what I mean?

187
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:25,000
 The people on the edges who don't quite fit in.

188
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:37,000
 And the church we were going to in Darwin, he noticed a young man who used to slip in sort of late and slip out early.

189
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:43,000
 And so my husband tracked him down and invited him for coffee.

190
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 And in that sharing, this man asked what we were doing and Glenn shared, "Oh, we're planning to go to Hong Kong.

191
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:56,000
 We want to work for this Christian NGO."

192
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 And this young man said to Glenn, "Oh, give me your banking details.

193
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:04,000
 I'd like to give you something towards that."

194
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 So Glenn did.

195
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 The next day, I remember Glenn rushing to me and saying, "Babe, look at this."

196
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:17,000
 And he showed me on the computer our bank balance.

197
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 And this young man had deposited $25,000 Australian dollars into our bank account.

198
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,000
 So we packed up from Darwin.

199
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 We travelled back to Queensland.

200
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 Queensland is where we are from.

201
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 And we were planning to go there to say our goodbyes to families, to wrap up loose ends and wait for our visas.

202
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
 And we began to wait.

203
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
 And we waited.

204
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:51,000
 And we waited some more.

205
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:55,000
 And we kept on waiting.

206
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,000
 We had four kids.

207
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,000
 I was trying to homeschool them.

208
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:07,000
 Yeah, all you kids, all you people with kids are going, "Ooh."

209
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:15,000
 We were moving every few weeks from this parent's home to that parent's home.

210
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:20,000
 And when I say that, there's four hours between those parents' home of travel.

211
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 We were going to people's farms.

212
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 We slept on mattresses on concrete floors.

213
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
 Weeks turned into months.

214
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:40,000
 I remember it got to eight months and there was still no sign of visas.

215
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 It's at moments like this in the waiting that we can struggle to feel God's presence.

216
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:54,000
 And the wait can make us feel like he's distant or maybe even absent.

217
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 And these moments offer us a choice.

218
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,000
 Do we lean in?

219
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:05,000
 Or do we lean out?

220
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,000
 And I chose to lean in.

221
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 I remember going into the downstairs bathroom of my parent's house, shutting the door.

222
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:20,000
 When you have kids, you know that this is one of the few places you can go to to escape.

223
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:28,000
 And I remember silently screaming out my frustrations to God, wrestling with him.

224
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,000
 "If you've called us, why?

225
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
 Why are we experiencing this?

226
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 How long, God?

227
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 How long?"

228
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:43,000
 And I remember saying to him, "I can't take this anymore.

229
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:50,000
 You're going to have to do something."

230
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:55,000
 I remember that the next week the visas came through.

231
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,000
 We were able to book our tickets and come.

232
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 I don't know all the reasons for the waiting.

233
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 But I can tell you that God's timing was perfect.

234
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 Our landlords, they came and picked us up from the airport.

235
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 I don't know what Hong Kong landlords do, but...

236
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 It's rare. Very rare.

237
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:28,000
 They came in a little green minivan and they picked us all up.

238
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 They took us to the house.

239
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 They had set up the house so that we had enough furniture and appliances...

240
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 ...so that we could start living in it straight away without having to race out to shops and get things.

241
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 And they had included toys for the kids.

242
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 Later on we were to discover that they attended a Seventh-day Adventist church.

243
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 And God had...just when they had heard our story...

244
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:05,000
 ...because we had met through this random Craigslist. They'd put their house on Craigslist at the time.

245
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 It was so weird. But Glenn had found it.

246
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,000
 And, you know, they'd asked why we were coming and we shared.

247
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:15,000
 And they said when they heard it they just knew.

248
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 They had to be a part of our story.

249
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 I guess because of all the transition the children had experienced in those eight months...

250
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:32,000
 ...of constant movement, they immediately settled.

251
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:37,000
 They immediately were at peace in our new home. I can't describe it.

252
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 It was just like they'd lived there forever.

253
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:46,000
 And our five-year-old who'd been waking every night since she'd been born...

254
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:55,000
 ...waking us multiple times and getting up to all sorts of mischief in the night.

255
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:59,000
 She slept through from her first night in Hong Kong.

256
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:03,000
 And she never woke again through the night.

257
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:08,000
 The waiting prepares you in ways you don't even know you need.

258
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:13,000
 The waiting forces you to trust if you let it.

259
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:16,000
 On the day of trouble you know...

260
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:23,000
 ...you intimately know the one who is alongside you and fighting for you.

261
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:29,000
 But what about the waiting that doesn't end?

262
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:34,000
 Come on, let's be real today.

263
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:38,000
 What about the spouse that never materialises?

264
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:42,000
 What about the child that never comes?

265
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 What about the one you love never finding Jesus?

266
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:52,000
 Or the one you love never regaining their faith?

267
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 What about the change that you long for?

268
00:21:55,000 --> 00:22:00,000
 The healing that you need not happening?

269
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:03,000
 What about this type of waiting?

270
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:10,000
 We're not talking about days or weeks. We're talking about years and decades.

271
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 This type of waiting there are not sufficient words to describe the ache that builds within you.

272
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 And this is what this series has revealed to me.

273
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 Andrew taught us that in God's eyes waiting is a gift.

274
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 A gift.

275
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:36,000
 How can this type of waiting be a gift?

276
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 He also taught us about kavah, the Hebrew word for waiting.

277
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:44,000
 To bind together, to gather together, to look, to expect.

278
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:48,000
 God's type of waiting calls us to...

279
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 ...remember all the promises and the hopes and the dreams and in them and through them...

280
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:58,000
 ...begin a process of anticipating all the good that is to come.

281
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 Hoping and expecting it'll come to pass.

282
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,000
 And God spoke to me in the night through my dreaming moments...

283
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:14,000
 ...and showed me that I was no longer anticipating my future.

284
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 The waiting, the longing, the ache in one area of my life, I no longer anticipated any change.

285
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:30,000
 I don't think I'm the only one in the room who is experiencing long-term waiting.

286
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:37,000
 I don't think I'm the only one here whose anticipation has died.

287
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:43,000
 Anticipation in the waiting for hopes, promises, dreams to come to pass.

288
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
 For change to come.

289
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:52,000
 You know when you examine your heart today that the length of the wait has crushed all expectation.

290
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:59,000
 You no longer eagerly anticipate God's intervention.

291
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:07,000
 The Bible says that hope deferred makes the heart sick.

292
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:12,000
 There have been many times over the course of the last 12 years that I've been waiting...

293
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 ...in one particular area of my life that I know my heart has been sick.

294
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 This type of waiting will challenge you to your core.

295
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,000
 It will strip you bare.

296
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:30,000
 It will leave you feeling incredibly vulnerable.

297
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 It'll cause you to question your faith.

298
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:40,000
 And if you're not careful it'll cause you to abandon it.

299
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:43,000
 It can numb you.

300
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:50,000
 Rob you of your joy, your sense of hope and your dreaming for change and a better future.

301
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:55,000
 I don't have all the answers for this type of waiting.

302
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 I'm still waiting.

303
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:09,000
 But I do know there are some things that I do know I have not been left alone in the waiting.

304
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:17,000
 I do know that I've come to experience deeper levels of God's comfort than I ever have before.

305
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:27,000
 I do know that I have a rich trust that I never would have had except for this journey.

306
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:33,000
 God has revealed himself time and time again in the waiting.

307
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:45,000
 Speaking words of comfort, reminding me of his nearness and challenging me and calling on me to deepen my trust.

308
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 I know I can give greater measures of love and grace away because I've experienced the depths of God's infinite grace.

309
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:10,000
 That picture in Ezekiel 47 where a man is led deeper and deeper into the water that is streaming from the temple, that picture of God's presence.

310
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:20,000
 The man gets led to a point where it is so deep, the only way he could possibly experience it is if he was to swim.

311
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:30,000
 This type of waiting where the answer does not come and a change has not happened, this type of waiting has taught me to swim.

312
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:38,000
 To have nothing to rely on to keep me up but the water, the presence of God.

313
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:45,000
 However, this doesn't just happen. You have a choice to make.

314
00:26:45,000 --> 00:27:02,000
 In these times of waiting, you can choose to lean in, to learn to trust God afresh and begin to anticipate afresh the future that he has for you.

315
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:14,000
 Or you can lean out, you can pull away and you can settle for substitutes.

316
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:24,000
 The third thing waiting does is remind us of his promises and heighten our gratitude.

317
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:34,000
 "Then my head will be exalted above the enemies who surround me, at his sacred tent I will sacrifice with shouts of joy, I will sing and make music to the Lord."

318
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:39,000
 When David sings this, he has not yet been delivered from his enemies.

319
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:48,000
 He is still surrounded but as he waits, he gets a glimpse of the good that is to come.

320
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:53,000
 He has the faith to declare that he will be delivered from his enemies.

321
00:27:53,000 --> 00:28:01,000
 His heart is filled with gratitude and joy as he's reminded of God's enduring presence and protection.

322
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 In the midst of the waiting, even before his release from his enemies, David breaks forth in shouts of joy, singing and praising God.

323
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:19,000
 Some of us today need to prophetically shout for joy and express our gratitude to God.

324
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:34,000
 Not because the answer has come, not because the waiting has ended, but because we believe in the one who is walking with us through the waiting.

325
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:37,000
 Waiting is for our benefit.

326
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:39,000
 God doesn't need it.

327
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:42,000
 He is ever present.

328
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:45,000
 But we take time.

329
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:54,000
 We take time for our minds to declutter and all the thoughts that are swirling around to settle.

330
00:28:54,000 --> 00:29:00,000
 Waiting, it realigns us to the one, the one thing that's needed.

331
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:04,000
 Waiting strengthens our resolve for future challenges.

332
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 And waiting reminds us of his promises and heightens our gratitude.

333
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:17,000
 Today we need to rediscover and truly value God's presence.

334
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:22,000
 We wait for what we value.

335
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 So how do we begin this process?

336
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 How do we restore our value that we hold in God?

337
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:41,000
 We start by removing the lesser things, the substitutes that have crowded our life and our mind and our hearts,

338
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:51,000
 stolen our time and caused us to drift away from what God truly intended for us.

339
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 I'm wearing a pair of Converse today.

340
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 See?

341
00:29:55,000 --> 00:30:00,000
 I bought them in Japan when my husband and I were there for our 30th wedding anniversary.

342
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:04,000
 I really, really wanted them.

343
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 But this store, I wanted a size 7.

344
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:13,000
 They only had 6.5 in the style that I wanted.

345
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:18,000
 And I didn't want to wait.

346
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 So I bought them.

347
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 And every time I wear them, I'm aware that I should have waited.

348
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:33,000
 My toes get a little bit pinched.

349
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:42,000
 And while we were in worship I was like, "I think the circulation is getting cut off."

350
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 I share this with you because if I hadn't told you, you wouldn't know.

351
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,000
 These shoes are like substitutes.

352
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 They aren't the ones that I should have had.

353
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:01,000
 They aren't the ones that would have been the right fit for me.

354
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 And many of us in here today, you've settled for substitutes.

355
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:11,000
 You've settled for lesser things.

356
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:14,000
 You're looking at the outside of your life and might not know.

357
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 But you do.

358
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 You do.

359
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:28,000
 It was like whenever I went out with somebody that I knew my parents didn't want me to go out with and they weren't a Christian, I would know.

360
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 I'd feel it.

361
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:34,000
 It's not quite the right fit.

362
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 So how do we respond to this?

363
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:43,000
 We have to remove the lesser things.

364
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:53,000
 I want us all to personally choose to create space here today to realign ourselves to the one thing that's needed.

365
00:31:53,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 If you're sitting here today and you know that you've taken paths that you shouldn't, that you've become impatient maybe in the waiting and have settled for a substitute or something lesser than what God intended for you, we're going to take some time now.

366
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 We're going to close our eyes.

367
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 And if that's you, I want you to open up your hands to be honest with God and say, "I want to begin the process of letting go of the lesser things, the things that have taken up my time and my energy and the paths I've walked that have not been the paths that I should have walked."

368
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:52,000
 Father, we open up our hands before you and we are all aware that at times we settle for substitutes.

369
00:32:52,000 --> 00:33:11,000
 We lose sight of the value of waiting for your intervention, waiting for you to bring the right fit, the right plans, the right person, the right job.

370
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:15,000
 And so we settle for substitutes.

371
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:19,000
 We settle for things that you never intended for us.

372
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:28,000
 So Father, right now we open up our hands as a sign to you that we're willing to let them go.

373
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:34,000
 We're willing to surrender them.

374
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 And Father, we pray right now that our value, the value we hold in our hearts of waiting on you, Father, we want to restore that today.

375
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:57,000
 We remind ourselves that those who wait, your word says they will be blessed.

376
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 We remind ourselves today that your word says that when we wait, you act on our behalf.

377
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 Father, thank you.

378
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:32,000
 Thank you for your goodness and your gentleness and your kindness that you wrap us up today.

379
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 I'd also now like to pray for those who have been waiting a long time.

380
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:45,000
 You've been waiting a long time for something.

381
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 And when I shared that God had revealed to me that I had stopped anticipating my future, you understood that.

382
00:34:55,000 --> 00:35:01,000
 You were sitting there thinking, yeah, I can't see a good future.

383
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 I can't see where change could possibly come from.

384
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:13,000
 I've lost all hope in God stepping in.

385
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 If that's you today, I'd like you to open up your hands.

386
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 Father, the waiting is painful, God.

387
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 But we remember today that we're not alone and that you understand our pain.

388
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 You understand our frame.

389
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:48,000
 You're familiar with all our ways.

390
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 You are not distant.

391
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:53,000
 You are in this.

392
00:35:53,000 --> 00:36:03,000
 So, Father, I pray right now for the ache and the pain that you would come and wrap us up in your tender love.

393
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 That we would have ears right now to hear your gentle whispers.

394
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:15,000
 That you would speak clearly to us.

395
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:20,000
 That you would give us the courage to deepen our trust.

396
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:33,000
 That the waiting is for our benefit and that good things can happen even in the middle of the waiting.

397
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 And lastly, we're going to stand in a minute.

398
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:45,000
 And we're going to take an opportunity to declare prophetically.

399
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:57,000
 Some of you today, you need to declare prophetically that you are going to trust the one who holds your future in his hands.

400
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:00,000
 You are going to trust that he is the God of the impossible.

401
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:04,000
 Even when you can't see how anything could happen or change or be different.

402
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 You're going to declare it prophetically.

403
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,000
 That you believe he's able.

404
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:12,000
 That he can do things that are beyond your understanding.

405
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:15,000
 And that you are going to trust him.

406
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,000
 I did this on the way to work this week.

407
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 And I began to declare to God that he is the God who can do things that I can't even imagine.

408
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:39,000
 That where my limitations were, I chose to prophetically declare that I wasn't going to let my limitations prevent me from believing and hoping and dreaming and trusting.

409
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 Today we're going to do that together.

410
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:47,000
 We're going to sing a song together that declares that.

411
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,000
 So would you stand with me?

412
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:52,580
 (gentle music)

